- Install postgres and create a 'geonames' database.
- Download Geonames from http://download.geonames.org/export/dump
- Run import-geonames.sh
- Create a geouser account with password geopw, grant permissions on the table:
  GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON geoname, admin1codes, countryInfo TO geouser
  (slightly excessive, it just needs to query)
- Install and configure Sphinx (/etc/sphinxsearch/sphinx.conf ) from universe.
- Create an index on geonameid which should reduce query times:
  CREATE INDEX geoname_id_idx ON geoname(geonameid);
- Install sphinxapi-python from ppa:~ev and use or modify the sphinx.conf
  provided.
- Install CherryPy from universe.
- Alternatively, install Apache and mod_python, then copy geoname-modpython.py
  to /var/www and edit the apache configuration:
  <Directory /var/www/>
        AddHandler mod_python .py
        PythonHandler geoname-modpython
        DirectoryIndex geoname-modpython.py
  </Directory>
- Run geoname.py, query with http://localhost:8080/?query=wandsworth
